text: Marion Francis Dolph (July 7, 1880 – November 11, 1921) was an American football player and coach. He served as the head football coach at the University of Oregon in 1902, compiling a record of 3–1–3. Dolph was a college football star at Williams College and the son of United States Senator Joseph N.
